            {
              "id": "CWE-51",
              "name": "PathEquivalenceMultipleInternalSlash",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The product accepts path input in the form of multiple internal slash ('/multiple//internal/slash/') without appropriate validation, which can lead to ambiguous path resolution and allow an attacker to traverse the file system to unintended locations or access arbitrary files."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The product accepts path input in the form of multiple internal slash ('/multiple//internal/slash/') without appropriate validation, which can lead to ambiguous path resolution and allow an attacker to traverse the file system to unintended locations or access arbitrary files.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe product accepts path input in the form of multiple internal slash ('/multiple//internal/slash/') without appropriate validation, which can lead to ambiguous path resolution and allow an attacker to traverse the file system to unintended locations or access arbitrary files.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Confidentiality, Integrity. **Impact**: Read Files or Directories, Modify Files or Directories.\n\n## Potential Mitigations\n\n1. *Phase: Implementation; Strategy: Input Validation*. Inputs should be decoded and canonicalized to the application's current internal representation before being validated (CWE-180). Make sure that the application does not decode the same input twice (CWE-174). Such errors could be used to bypass allowlist validation schemes by introducing dangerous inputs after they have been checked."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/51.html",
              "properties": {
