            {
              "id": "CWE-1056",
              "name": "InvokableControlElementWithVariadicParameters",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A named-callable or method control element has a signature that supports a variable (variadic) number of parameters or arguments."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "A named-callable or method control element has a signature that supports a variable (variadic) number of parameters or arguments.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nA named-callable or method control element has a signature that supports a variable (variadic) number of parameters or arguments.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Reliability.\n  - This issue can prevent the product from running reliably. If the relevant code is reachable by an attacker, then this reliability problem might introduce a vulnerability. With variadic arguments, it can be difficult or inefficient for manual analysis to be certain of which function/method is being invoked."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1056.html",
