            {
              "id": "CWE-1063",
              "name": "CreationOfClassInstanceWithinAStaticCodeBlock",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A static code block creates an instance of a class."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "This pattern identifies situations where a storable data element or member data element is initialized with a value in a block of code which is declared as static."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "A static code block creates an instance of a class.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nA static code block creates an instance of a class.\n\n## Extended Description\n\nThis pattern identifies situations where a storable data element or member data element is initialized with a value in a block of code which is declared as static.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Performance.\n  - This issue can make the product perform more slowly by performing initialization before it is needed. If the relevant code is reachable by an attacker, then this performance problem might introduce a vulnerability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1063.html",
              "properties": {
                "cwe/title": "Creation of Class Instance within a Static Code Block",
                "cwe/status": "Incomplete",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Base",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-1176"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1064",
              "name": "InvokableControlElementWithSignatureContainingAnExcessiveNumberOfParameters",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The product contains a function, subroutine, or method whose signature has an unnecessarily large number of parameters/arguments."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "While the interpretation of \"large number of parameters\" may vary for each product or developer, CISQ recommends a default maximum of 7 parameters/arguments."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The product contains a function, subroutine, or method whose signature has an unnecessarily large number of parameters/arguments.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe product contains a function, subroutine, or method whose signature has an unnecessarily large number of parameters/arguments.\n\n## Extended Description\n\nWhile the interpretation of \"large number of parameters\" may vary for each product or developer, CISQ recommends a default maximum of 7 parameters/arguments.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Maintainability, Increase Analytical Complexity.\n  - This issue makes it more difficult to understand and/or maintain the product, which indirectly affects security by making it more difficult or time-consuming to find and/or fix vulnerabilities. It also might make it easier to introduce vulnerabilities."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1064.html",
