            {
              "id": "CWE-1068",
              "name": "InconsistencyBetweenImplementationAndDocumentedDesign",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The implementation of the product is not consistent with the design as described within the relevant documentation."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The implementation of the product is not consistent with the design as described within the relevant documentation.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe implementation of the product is not consistent with the design as described within the relevant documentation.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Maintainability, Increase Analytical Complexity.\n  - This issue makes it more difficult to maintain the product due to inconsistencies, which indirectly affects security by making it more difficult or time-consuming to find and/or fix vulnerabilities. It also might make it easier to introduce vulnerabilities."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1068.html",
