            {
              "id": "CWE-1083",
              "name": "DataAccessFromOutsideExpectedDataManagerComponent",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The product is intended to manage data access through a particular data manager component such as a relational or non-SQL database, but it contains code that performs data access operations without using that component."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "When the product has a data access component, the design may be intended to handle all data access operations through that component. If a data access operation is performed outside of that component, then this may indicate a violation of the intended design."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The product is intended to manage data access through a particular data manager component such as a relational or non-SQL database, but it contains code that performs data access operations without using that component.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe product is intended to manage data access through a particular data manager component such as a relational or non-SQL database, but it contains code that performs data access operations without using that component.\n\n## Extended Description\n\nWhen the product has a data access component, the design may be intended to handle all data access operations through that component. If a data access operation is performed outside of that component, then this may indicate a violation of the intended design.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Reliability.\n  - This issue can prevent the product from running reliably. If the relevant code is reachable by an attacker, then this reliability problem might introduce a vulnerability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1083.html",
