              "help": {
                "text": "The source code contains elements such as source files that do not consistently provide a prologue or header that has been standardized for the project.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe source code contains elements such as source files that do not consistently provide a prologue or header that has been standardized for the project.\n\n## Extended Description\n\nStandard prologues or headers may contain information such as module name, version number, author, date, purpose, function, assumptions, limitations, accuracy considerations, etc.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Maintainability.\n  - This issue makes it more difficult to maintain the product due to insufficient analyzability, which indirectly affects security by making it more difficult or time-consuming to find and/or fix vulnerabilities. It also might make it easier to introduce vulnerabilities.\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Increase Analytical Complexity.\n  - The lack of a prologue can make it more difficult to accurately and quickly understand the associated code."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1115.html",
              "properties": {
                "cwe/title": "Source Code Element without Standard Prologue",
                "cwe/status": "Incomplete",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Base",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-1078"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1116",
              "name": "InaccurateSourceCodeComments",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The source code contains comments that do not accurately describe or explain aspects of the portion of the code with which the comment is associated."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The source code contains comments that do not accurately describe or explain aspects of the portion of the code with which the comment is associated.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe source code contains comments that do not accurately describe or explain aspects of the portion of the code with which the comment is associated.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Maintainability.\n  - This issue makes it more difficult to maintain the product, which indirectly affects security by making it more difficult or time-consuming to find and/or fix vulnerabilities. It also might make it easier to introduce vulnerabilities.\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Increase Analytical Complexity.\n  - When a comment does not accurately reflect the associated code elements, this can introduce confusion to a reviewer (due to inconsistencies) or make it more difficult and less efficient to validate that the code is implementing the intended behavior correctly.\n\n## Potential Mitigations\n\n1. *Phase: Implementation*. Verify that each comment accurately reflects what is intended to happen during execution of the code."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1116.html",
              "properties": {
                "cwe/title": "Inaccurate Source Code Comments",
                "cwe/status": "Incomplete",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Base",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-1078"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1117",
              "name": "CallableWithInsufficientBehavioralSummary",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The code contains a function or method whose signature and/or associated inline documentation does not sufficiently describe the callable's inputs, outputs, side effects, assumptions, or return codes."
              },
              "help": {
