                "cwe/title": "ASP.NET Misconfiguration: Improper Model Validation",
                "cwe/status": "Draft",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Variant",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-1173"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1176",
              "name": "InefficientCpuComputation",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The product performs CPU computations using algorithms that are not as efficient as they could be for the needs of the developer, i.e., the computations can be optimized further."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The product performs CPU computations using algorithms that are not as efficient as they could be for the needs of the developer, i.e., the computations can be optimized further.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe product performs CPU computations using algorithms that are not as efficient as they could be for the needs of the developer, i.e., the computations can be optimized further.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Availability. **Impact**: Reduce Performance, DoS: Resource Consumption (CPU).\n  - This issue can make the product perform more slowly, possibly in ways that are noticeable to the users. If an attacker can influence the amount of computation that must be performed, e.g. by triggering worst-case complexity, then this performance problem might introduce a vulnerability."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1176.html",
              "properties": {
                "cwe/title": "Inefficient CPU Computation",
                "cwe/status": "Incomplete",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Class",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-405"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1177",
              "name": "UseOfProhibitedCode",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "The product uses a function, library, or third party component that has been explicitly prohibited, whether by the developer or the customer."
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "The developer - or customers - may wish to restrict or eliminate use of a function, library, or third party component for any number of reasons, including real or suspected vulnerabilities; difficulty to use securely; export controls or license requirements; obsolete or poorly-maintained code; internal code being scheduled for deprecation; etc. To reduce risk of vulnerabilities, the developer might maintain a list of \"banned\" functions that programmers must avoid using because the functions are difficult or impossible to use securely. This issue can also make the product more costly and difficult to maintain."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "The product uses a function, library, or third party component that has been explicitly prohibited, whether by the developer or the customer.",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nThe product uses a function, library, or third party component that has been explicitly prohibited, whether by the developer or the customer.\n\n## Extended Description\n\nThe developer - or customers - may wish to restrict or eliminate use of a function, library, or third party component for any number of reasons, including real or suspected vulnerabilities; difficulty to use securely; export controls or license requirements; obsolete or poorly-maintained code; internal code being scheduled for deprecation; etc. To reduce risk of vulnerabilities, the developer might maintain a list of \"banned\" functions that programmers must avoid using because the functions are difficult or impossible to use securely. This issue can also make the product more costly and difficult to maintain.\n\n## Common Consequences\n\n- **Scope**: Other. **Impact**: Reduce Maintainability.\n\n## Potential Mitigations\n\n1. *Phase: Build and Compilation, Implementation*. Identify a list of prohibited API functions and prohibit developers from using these functions, providing safer alternatives. In some cases, automatic code analysis tools or the compiler can be instructed to spot use of prohibited functions, such as the \"banned.h\" include file from Microsoft's SDL. [REF-554] [REF-1009] [REF-7]"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/1177.html",
              "properties": {
                "cwe/title": "Use of Prohibited Code",
                "cwe/status": "Incomplete",
                "cwe/abstraction": "Class",
                "cwe/parent": "CWE-710"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CWE-1187",
              "name": "DeprecatedUseOfUninitializedResource",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "This entry has been deprecated because it was a duplicate of CWE-908."
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "This entry has been deprecated because it was a duplicate of CWE-908. All content has been transferred to CWE-908.",
